1 (2) names of persons committed to the provision of library services and living in the
2 county in which the vacancy occurred unless the fiscal court has adopted an
3 alternative appointment process through the passage of a resolution. For fiscal
4 courts that adopt an alternative appointment process, the county judge/executive[:
5 (a) 1. May immediately, with the approval of the fiscal court, make the
6 appointment on the recommendation of the state librarian and
7 commissioner of two (2) names of persons committed to the provision
8 of library services and living in the county in which the vacancy
9 occurred; and
10 2. If the county judge/executive decides not to make the appointment from
11 the first recommendations, shall request the Department for Libraries
12 and Archives to submit within thirty (30) days two (2) additional
13 recommended persons for the unfilled appointment, and, with the
14 approval of the fiscal court, may make the selection from those
15 recommendations; and
16 (b) For any remaining unfilled appointment after the provisions of paragraph (a)
17 of this subsection have been followed,] shall appoint, with the approval of the
18 fiscal court, an individual of his or her choosing no later than sixty (60)[thirty
19 (30)] days after the vacancy occurred[day the county judge/executive
20 received the recommendations under paragraph (a)2. of this subsection and
21 made no appointment therefrom]. Any person appointed in accordance with
22 this subsection[paragraph] shall be committed to the provision of library
23 services and living in the county in which the vacancy occurred. The county
24 judge/executive shall notify the Department for Libraries and Archives of the
25 name of any individual appointed by the alternative process[in the manner set
26 out in this paragraph].
27 (3) A member of the board may be removed from office as provided by KRS 65.007.
